Doc states: `by delivering 1 header initially and then the rest`. Could we clarify this by code instead?
We don't really have `head`/`tail` like in many functional programming languages, but maybe we could do:
```C++
    const std::span headers_batch{second_chain};
    (void)hss->ProcessNextHeaders(headers_batch.first(1), true);
...
    result = hss->ProcessNextHeaders(headers_batch.last(headers_batch.size() - 1), false);
```

